    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1999_Solutions_1999s_page_002_24",
    "text": "Thus it suffices to prove that if Q(x) is a monic polynomial of degree 1999 with all of its roots in (0, 1], then So |Q(x)|dx ≥ D for some constant D > 0. But the integral of So 11191 x-rildx is a continuous function for ri € (0, 1). The product of all of these intervals is compact, so the integral achieves a minimum value for some ri. This minimum is the desired D.",
